column10:
this is a good third game in the series, lives up to it's predecessors. The main story's ending was a true emotional trip, definitely a 10/10.But I can say that it exceeds the past games on the DLCs (the main story is still better than the DLCs obviously), last light's has a decent amount of extra DLC stories (6 stories if i remember correctly) but I played none of them, couldn't be bother to play them as they weren't that interesting as the main story. But the DLCs in Exodus lives up to the main story. 

*Sam's story is great as it brings a closure to our american trapped in post-apocalyptic russia, it's a story about to whether be a hero, a great man or salvation for your dreams. it's a good moral choice that test the player's choice.

*The two colonel is a story about a man becoming great in a tragic world that's full of selfishness, it's a tragic story and really sad one, made me tear up. Definitely a good DLC, Kirill better eat those liver ;-;
